{"id":"7015","name":"Remove Diacritics [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to remove diacritics from a text","icon":"ios12 c255 g59853","latest":"21789","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A single line of JavaScript that removes the diacritics from a text. Much simpler than replacing all the possible combinations of letter+diacritic, all thanks to the <a href=\"https://www.unicode.org/faq/normalization.html\">Unicode NFD normalization</a>. This can be used to improve comparison/search, or to generate less problematic filenames.</p>\n<p>A variation of this code was the ingredient in my <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/4268/\"><em>Unicode Font Variants</em> shortcut</a> that allowed me to replace each letter while keeping their diacritics. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>No error checking</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20font%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20remove%20diacritics%20from%20a%20text%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20(2020-10-12)%5Cn%5Cn-%20This%20can%20be%20used%20to%20improve%20comparison%2Fsearch%2C%20or%20to%20generate%20less%20problematic%20filenames%5Cn-%20No%20error%20checking%22%0AText%20%22Ma%C3%B1ana%20Voil%C3%A0%20Ch%C3%A2teau%20Fra%C3%BClein%20Caf%C3%A9%20Fa%C3%A7ade%22%20-%3E%20mv%3AText%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%3Bcharset%3Dutf-8%2C%3Cscript%3Edocument.write(%60%5C(mv%3AText)%60.normalize(%5C%22NFD%5C%22).replace(%2F%5B%5C%5Cu0300-%5C%5Cu036f%5D%2Fg%2C%20%5C%22%5C%22))%3B%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%0AGetFileofType%20type%3D%22com.apple.webarchive%22%20-%3E%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%0AShowAlert%20title%3D%22Texto%20Modificado%22%20message%3D%22Input%3A%5Cn%5C(mv%3AText)%5Cn%5CnOutput%3A%5Cn%5C(mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%7Bas%3A%20text%7D)%22%20showCancelButton%3Dfalse\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/normalize\"><code>String.prototype.normalize()</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html;charset=utf-8,&lt;script&gt;document.write(`REPLACETHISWITHTEXTVARIABLE`.normalize(\"NFD\").replace(/[\\u0300-\\u036f]/g, \"\"))&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Replace the <code>REPLACETHISWITHTEXTVARIABLE</code> fragment with the variable contaning the text, add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and interpret its output as text.</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Oct. 12, 2020, 3:53 p.m.</strong></p>"}